2. **No positive pattern** — every JSON example and template (`SKILL.md:922/938/958/962/966`) links a path *only* as the leading finding location; the example summary sentences never contain a reference. The templates teach the backticked/location-only form, and the "link mentions in prose" mandate loses to them — the exact dynamic the test header records ("the body templates demonstrated the backticked form, so the inlined mandate lost").

**Over-linking guard (why this isn't just "link everything"):** the fortune-os comment itself shows the boundary the model must keep — `apps/boilerplate/features/steps/steps.ts` is a real repo file (→ link) but `*.steps.ts` in the same sentence is a glob pattern (→ stays backticked). Broadening the self-check to no-line-number paths without an explicit code-specimen carve-out would regress into linking globs, config keys (`agents.trackers`), bare directories, and illustrative names. RFC-0001's own rule already draws the line — "a token named only as an example, with no real target, is a code specimen" — so the fix must both broaden the trigger AND state the carve-out, gated on the existing "Only resolvable targets" check (a glob/pattern/key resolves to no repo blob, so it is never linked).

This is a prompt-only fix (user-selected), matching the existing prompt-driven design; no code-side linkifier. Note: this is the third recurrence of this class (replies #387, locations #406, now prose mentions) — if it recurs after this, a deterministic code-side linkifier in `reviewOutput.ts` becomes the fallback.

## Implementation Steps

All prompt edits are in `claude-plugins/autopilot/skills/pr:review/SKILL.md`, in the "File and doc links" block (`:891–897`) and the approve-with-suggestions example (`:938`). Exact replacement text below; the surrounding block and the canonical RFC-0001 sentinel block (`:1020–1038`) are untouched, so `referenceFormattingSync` stays green.

1. **Broaden the "Locations and mentions" bullet** (`SKILL.md:893`) so a no-line-number prose mention links too, and a bare RFC links its doc even when the `§X` anchor is unresolvable. Replace the bullet with:
   > - **Locations and mentions** — every finding location AND every file/doc/RFC mention in prose renders as a link, wherever it appears: the leading finding location, the summary sentence, mid-description text, and inside `inlineComments` bodies. With a known line: `[<path>:<NN>](<pr-blob-url>/<path>#L<NN>)` (ranges `#L<start>-L<end>`). With no line — a plain prose mention of a repo file/doc — drop the fragment and still link the path: `[<path>](<pr-blob-url>/<path>)`. A bare `RFC-NNNN` links to its doc via the [§1.4](#14-project-context-read-before-reviewing) standards inventory even when a trailing `§X` section anchor is unresolvable (link the document; omit the anchor).
   - verify: `grep -c "summary sentence" SKILL.md` ≥ 1 and the bullet shows the `[<path>](<pr-blob-url>/<path>)` no-line form.

2. **Add the code-specimen carve-out** to the "Only resolvable targets" bullet (`SKILL.md:894`) — append one sentence after "…worse than no link.":
   > A token that is not a real target — a glob or pattern (`*.steps.ts`), a bare directory, a config key (`agents.trackers`), or an illustrative name that resolves to no repo blob — is a code specimen, not a reference: keep it backticked and never link it.
   - verify: `grep -q "code specimen, not a reference" SKILL.md`.

3. **Close the self-check gap** (`SKILL.md:897`) — replace the Self-check bullet with:
   > - **Self-check** — before emitting the structured output, scan the entire `reviewComment` (including the summary sentence, not just finding lines) and every `inlineComments` body: outside code spans/fences, any resolvable repo-relative file or doc path — with OR without a line number — a bare `RFC-NNNN` id, or a bare 7–40-char hex token is a violation unless it is one of the two allowed forms above (inline own anchor; unresolvable/no-blob-at-head path). Link paths per these rules and SHAs as `https://github.com/<REPO>/commit/<sha>`. A path that resolves to no repo blob (a glob, pattern, config key, or illustrative name) is NOT a violation — leave it backticked.
   - verify: the gating phrase "file path with a line number" is gone; "with OR without a line number" and "including the summary sentence" are present.

4. **Rewrite the approve-with-suggestions example** (`SKILL.md:938`) so it models the discrimination — a linked doc in the **summary sentence**, a linked cross-file mention **with no line number mid-description**, and a **backticked glob specimen left alone**. Replace the `reviewComment` value with:
   > `"Points the retry policy in [docs/webhooks.md](<pr-blob-url>/docs/webhooks.md) at the new handler.\n\n### 🙋‍♂️ Suggestions\n\n- [src/webhooks/payment.ts:62](<pr-blob-url>/src/webhooks/payment.ts#L62) - Consider exponential backoff; the \`retry*\` helpers in [src/webhooks/config.ts](<pr-blob-url>/src/webhooks/config.ts) still assume single-attempt delivery [CHECK-ARCH-002](<RULES_DOC_URL>#CHECK-ARCH-002)\n- [docs/webhooks.md:12](<pr-blob-url>/docs/webhooks.md?plain=1#L12) - Retry policy chapter still documents single-attempt delivery [CHECK-DOC-001](<RULES_DOC_URL>#CHECK-DOC-001)\n\n### 👍 Approve"`
   - The `inlineComments` array and rule-code suffixes stay as-is. The linked leading-location forms are preserved, so the existing negative guards (banning backticked `` `src/webhooks/payment.ts:62` ``) still hold.
   - verify: the example contains `[docs/webhooks.md](<pr-blob-url>/docs/webhooks.md)` (summary, no line), `[src/webhooks/config.ts](<pr-blob-url>/src/webhooks/config.ts)` (mid-description, no line), and a backticked `` `retry*` `` specimen.

5. **Pin the fix with a guard test** in `.github/actions/code-review-action/src/prBodyReferenceFormatting.test.ts`, added to the `describe("review body file links")` block (~`:85`):
   ```ts
   test("links no-line prose/summary mentions while sparing code-specimen paths", async () => {
     const content = await readFile(reviewSkill, "utf8");
     // self-check broadened: covers no-line mentions and the summary sentence
     expect(content).toContain("with OR without a line number");
     expect(content).toContain("including the summary sentence");
     // example models a linked doc in the summary + a linked no-line file mention in prose
     expect(content).toContain("[docs/webhooks.md](<pr-blob-url>/docs/webhooks.md)");
     expect(content).toContain("[src/webhooks/config.ts](<pr-blob-url>/src/webhooks/config.ts)");
     // globs/keys stay backticked, not linked
     expect(content).toContain("code specimen, not a reference");
   });
   ```
   - Leave the existing presence/negative guards (`:88–115`) unchanged.
   - verify: `bun test src/prBodyReferenceFormatting.test.ts` passes from `.github/actions/code-review-action`.

## Files

- `claude-plugins/autopilot/skills/pr:review/SKILL.md:893–897` — broaden the Locations/mentions bullet (step 1), add the code-specimen carve-out (step 2), close the Self-check gap (step 3); rewrite the approve example `reviewComment` at `:938` (step 4).
- `.github/actions/code-review-action/src/prBodyReferenceFormatting.test.ts:85` — one new positive guard test (step 5).

